body.content:
You are writing a payment reminder email.

CRITICAL RULES (must follow):
- Use ONLY the invoice details listed below. Do NOT guess, infer, or invent any missing information.
- If a detail is missing/blank, omit that detail entirely (do not add placeholders like [Customer Name]).
- Do not mention tracking numbers, products/services, dates, or amounts unless they appear below exactly.
- If the customer name is missing, start the email with "Hello," (no name).

Invoice details (may be blank):
You are writing a payment reminder email for {{quickbooks.CustomerRef.name}}

Invoice details:
- Invoice #: {{quickbooks.DocNumber}} 
- Line Item: {{quickbooks.Line[0].SalesItemLineDetail.ItemRef.name}}
- Amount due: {{quickbooks.TotalAmt}}
- Due date: {{quickbooks.DueDate}} 
- Tracking Number: {{quickbooks.TrackingNum}}

Write a short email (3-4 sentences) that:
- If Product/Service is present, reference it; otherwise say "your invoice".
- If Invoice total is present, state it; otherwise do not mention an amount.
- If Due date is present, state it; otherwise do not mention a due date.

Output only the email body. No subject line. No signoff.
